, "aqueous": true, "other": "anoxic"}, "mechanism": "CO2 is reduced by H2 over magnetite/pyrite surfaces to acetate (part of Fischer\u2013Tropsch-type process).", "reasoning": "Supported by hydrothermal vent experiments and Fischer\u2013Tropsch-type reducing systems (He et al. 2010)."}, {"id": "rxn_002", "name": "Acetate and CO2 to pyruvate", "inputs": ["mol_005", "mol_001", "mol_002"], "outputs": ["mol_004"], "environment": "Hydrothermal", "agents": ["greigite"], "conditions": {"temperature": "350-400K", "pressure": "high", "catalyst": "greigite", "aqueous": true, "other": "anoxic"}, "mechanism": "Stepwise carboxylation and reduction of acetate with CO2 and H2 to pyruvate on greigite surfaces.", "reasoning": "In line with (Huber & W\u00e4chtersh\u00e4user, 1997; Cody et al., 2000) for prebiotic pyruvate synthesis via carbon fixation on FeS/Greigite."}, {"id": "rxn_003", "name": "Pyruvate to acetaldehyde via decarboxylation", "inputs": ["mol_004"], "outputs": ["mol_006", "mol_001"], "environment": "Hydrothermal", "agents": ["greigite"], "conditions": {"temperature": "350-420K", "pressure": "moderate-high", "catalyst": "greigite", "aqueous": true, "other": "thermal"}, "mechanism": "Pyruvate undergoes mineral-catalyzed decarboxylation to acetaldehyde.", "reasoning": "Supported by Huber & W\u00e4chtersh\u00e4user, 1997 for FeS-catalyzed decarboxylation of keto acids."}, {"id": "rxn_004", "name": "Aldol condensation: glycolaldehyde formation", "inputs": ["mol_007"], "outputs": ["mol_008"], "environment": "Surface", "agents": ["borate minerals", "montmorillonite"], "conditions": {"temperature": "300-350K", "pressure": "ambient", "catalyst": "borate/montmorillonite", "aqueous": true, "other": "wet-dry cycles"}, "mechanism": "Glycolic acid (hydrothermal) dehydrated and concentrated on mineral surfaces to glycolaldehyde.", "reasoning": "Borate stabilizes sugars; see (Kim et al., 2011) and (Benner et al., 2012)."}, {"id": "rxn_005", "name": "Formose reaction: formaldehyde to